title: Serialize/FunctionDefinition-normalized-nested
description: AST-only mode preserves indented nested definitions verbatim, normalizes the pragma gap and drops the named end marker
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

`\end alpha` becomes a bare `\end`, and the pragma is followed by a blank
line; the indented nested definitions inside the body stay verbatim.

Why: the definition text is stored verbatim in the AST, nested definitions
included, but the named end marker and the single newline after the pragma
are not recorded.

* Covers: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/fnprocdef.js and $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/whitespace.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
+
title: Input
mode: ast-only

\whitespace trim
\procedure alpha(x)
    \procedure beta(y)
    <$text text=<<y>>/>
    \end beta
    \procedure beta(y)
        <$text text=<<y>>/>
    \end beta
<$transclude $variable="beta" y={{{ [<x>addprefix<x>] }}}/>
\end alpha

<<alpha "Elephant">>
